mrigger added on 2019-10-09 20:33:43:
Consider the following test case:
CREATE TABLE t0(c1);
CREATE TABLE t1(c0);
CREATE VIEW v0 AS SELECT c1 FROM t1 LEFT JOIN t0;
INSERT INTO t1 VALUES (1);
SELECT * FROM v0 WHERE NOT(v0.c1 IS FALSE); -- expected: row is fetched, actual: no row is fetched
I would expect the row to be fetched, because the condition evaluates to TRUE for the row:
SELECT NOT(v0.c1 IS FALSE) FROM v0; -- 1
